@snairin - Thanks, and Happy New Year to you too.

@eculeader - If a movie's aspect ratio is 16:9 you will see the black letterbox bars whether they are encoded into the video or not, unless:-

1. Your monitor has a screen resolution equal to 16:9 (which it won't have).
2. The movie's aspect ratio is 4:3, and not 16:9.
3. The movie's width has been cropped, rendering it not 1080p/720p.
4. Your monitor has a zoom facility.

It just so happens that AVCHD format REQUIRES full 1920x1080 or 1280x720 resolution to work, otherwise it throws the aspect ratio out, but there is nothing to be gained by removing "black screen bull" as you call it. And since when did a movie's aspect ratio have anything to do with a video's resolution anyway?

You really should do your homework before you post such ignorant comments, or stick to downloading things you know something about, like ebooks on stupidity?

